<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="B" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Blend" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Blend</orth> (partic. <cit><quote>blended,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tro 4.5.86" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. IV, 5, 86</bibl></cit> and <bibl n="shak. cor 3.1.103" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. III, 1, 103</bibl>; <cit><quote>blent,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mv 3.2.183" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. III, 2, 183</bibl></cit> and <bibl n="shak. tn 1.5.257" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. I, 5, 257</bibl>) 1) to mix: <bibl n="shak. mv 3.2.183" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. III, 2, 183</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 1.5.257" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. I, 5, 257</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 4.5.86" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. IV, 5, 86</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 3.1.103" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. III, 1, 103</bibl>.<lb />2) intr. to mingle: <emph>the heaven-hued sapphire</emph> <cit><quote>and the opal b. with objects manifold,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lc 215" default="NO" valid="yes">Compl. 215</bibl></cit> (according to Walker, <emph>blend</emph> is here a participle, == blent).
